EmailTemplate.name: 2008 ASA Symposium - Thank you for registering
EmailTemplate.subject: Thank you for registering to attend the American Student Assistance 2008 Symposium
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.FirstName},
We are excited about the great program we have planned for this year’s American Student Assistance Symposium and are happy that you will be joining us.
For your convenience, we have included some important details that should make your visit to Boston easier and more enjoyable.
This year's Symposium will once again be held at The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel and Boston Convention and Exhibition Center EAST (BCEC). The dates are Monday and Tuesday June 16 and 17, 2008.
If you are arriving on Sunday, June 15, 2008, please plan to join us for the early registration and informal welcome reception which will be held in The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel on the lower level, please look for signs and ASA greeters who will direct you to the area.
Monday and Tuesday, June 16 and 17, 2008, all Symposium sessions will take place in the BCEC EAST, which is accessible from The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel via the walkway on the second level. For your convenience, greeters and signs will be able to direct you to the Convention Center.
On Monday evening, please plan to join us for a traditional New England clambake at The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel tent, located outside on the lower level. The reception will begin at 5:30 p.m. with clambake directly following. Attire for this event will be causal.
Directions to The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel & Boston Convention and Exhibition Center:
General Directions to The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel 425 Summer Street · Boston, Massachusetts 02210 · Phone: (617) 532-4600
General Parking Directions
Parking is available at both The Westin and the Convention Center South Lot (see attached map)
Parking cost: The Westin Boston Waterfront Hotel: All day, self parking: $31 Over night, self parking: $29 24-hour valet with in-and-out privileges: $41
Convention Center South Lot: All day, self parking: $10 All day, valet: $20
If you are taking public transportation, the MBTA Silver Line Waterfront Service - bus routes 7 and 11 from South Station, will get you to the hotel and convention center.
Please be sure to check out www.amsa.com for recent updates to the Symposium agenda.
If you have any questions, please contact me at 800-999-9080, extension 4207. We look forward to seing you!
Best regards,
Nancy Meehan Marketing Events Manager American Student Assistance
